The paper discusses the design and evaluation of field-normalized scientometric indicators, which are commonly used in the field of computer science to compare research units in different scientific fields. The paper focuses on issues related to publication, collaboration, and citation practices, which are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
